The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Culture board 

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Oct. 11: The Union ministry for culture has for the first time constituted a central advisory board for aiding it in evolving programmes that will integrate the diverse Indian culture.

 Headed by Union minister for culture S. Jaipal Reddy, the board will comprise Dr Kapila Vatsyayan (vice-chairman), Prof. Yashpal, Prof. Mrinal Miri, Adoor Gopalakrishnan, Shyam Benegal, Ramchandra Guha, Ayyappa Panikkar, Ranesh Ray and Prof. Mohammad Amin.

 Identifying the human repositories of the different facets of culture, the Central Advisory Board on Culture will advise the government on strategies to ensure there is continuity in their development. 

 It will focus on creativity in culture at different levels that have been neglected or not sustained through the existing institutional mechanisms.

 The board will coordinate the functions of each body under the ministry and examine how various aspects of Indian culture are being addressed by the agencies concerned. It will also help provide inputs for the formulation of need-based programmes and guide the work of the National Missions set up by the ministry.




